item.title: Why doesn't anyone help me?
item.dc:creator: @austinx austinx
item.description:
@austinx wrote:

if you dedicated and not lazy there’s common mistakes such as going to gui and adding your ip then go to client and add your no-ip in there.
then compile make a download for that and then set the ip back to 127.0.0.1
also go to http://www.canyouseeme.org/
and where it says 80 type in 43594 and if it says success then you’ve portfowarded correct if it fails try portfowarding again if you have a belkin router i can help if not i’ll try my best for further questions add my skype : austin.brown125
